    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at some paperwork for a shipment from ningbo and i'm a bit confused. can u explain the main difference between CIF and FOB under incoterms 2020? specifically who handles the insurance and when does the risk actually transfer to us?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The main difference between CIF and FOB lies in where the seller's responsibility ends and your responsibility begins. With FOB, you take over the risk and cost of shipping once the goods are loaded onto the vessel in Ningbo. Conversely, CIF requires the seller to cover the cost of freight and insurance up to the named port of destination, meaning they handle insurance until the cargo arrives.",
      "source": "target",
