    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. one more thing—what happens if the cargo is lost due to something like heavy storms or some kind of unforeseen maritime accident? i'm just worried about those \"mystery\" scenarios where things just vanish at sea or get damaged in ways that are hard to prove. are there specific clauses we should look for in the CIF contract to cover those kinds of unpredictable losses?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For those unpredictable losses at sea, the level of coverage in the insurance policy is crucial, not just the Incoterm itself. You should look for a policy that offers \"All Risks\" coverage, rather than just \"Named Perils,\" as \"All Risks\" covers a much broader range of unexpected damage. If the seller has secured adequate insurance under CIF, they should have documentation verifying this extensive coverage to protect against those mystery losses.",
      "source": "target",
